One-liner in Java, using the fact that A[0]...A[i-1] can be computed using the product before i. (i.e. from left to right) then A[i+1]...A[n] can be computed using the product after i.   
public int[] productExceptSelf(int[] nums) {   
int[] output = new int[nums.length];   
int product = 1;   
for (int i = 0; i < nums.length; i++) {   
output[i] = product;   
product *= nums[i];   
}   
product = 1;   
for (int i = nums.length-1; i >= 0; i--) {   
output[i] *= product;   
product *= nums[i];   
}   
return output;   
}   
