Here is an (I think) O(n) space and O(n) time solution, (but with a twist): Each element of the output array keeps track of the product before itself instead of after. (And then the output array is computed again).   
So A[i] now denotes A[0] .. A[i-1] and therefore   
A[n-2] = A[0] ... A[n-3]   
A[n-1] = A[0] ... A[n-2]   
This means that the first element is still 1.   
public int[] productExceptSelf(int[] nums) {   
int[] output = new int[nums.length];   
int product = 1;   
for (int i = 0; i < nums.length; i++) {   
output[i] = product;   
product *= nums[i];   
}   
product = 1;   
for (int i = nums.length-1; i >= 0; i--) {   
output[i] *= product;   
product *= nums[i];   
}   
return output;   
}   
